  "body": "The docs advise Truffle 5 plugin users to set their solc config like this.\r\n```javascript\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solc: { version: \"0.5.2\" }\r\n};\r\n```\r\nHowever it looks like buidler automatically sets the `evmVersion` to 'petersburg' triggering this error:\r\n```shell\r\nInvalid EVM version requested.\r\nError BDLR600: Compilation failed\r\n```\r\nbecause solc didn't start supporting it until [`0.5.5`](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/releases/tag/v0.5.5)? Not sure. It might be possible semver check the compiler version when the evmVersion isn't specified and pick the best guess. \r\n\r\nA workaround is to use `0.5.5` or later.\r\n",
